t=\"12198090531909861341man silhouette.svg.hi\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Robert boasts 8 years of commercial interior architectural experience across a range of disciplines, 6 years of residential design.This gives him a very strong experience in both fields combined. His background experience is very much influenced by his training, working with some of the worlds leading design companies such as HOK, and Gensler. Previous clients include Apple, Cisco, Clifford Chance to name a few.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Andraya Smith - Design Assistant</p>\r\n<p class=\"articleCaption\" style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-190 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/12198090531909861341man-silhouette.svg_.hi_-150x150.png\" alt=\"12198090531909861341man silhouette.svg.hi\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />After studying fashion in both London and Tokyo, Andraya Smith returned to the United States to pursue a career in fashion. In Miami, she successfully worked as a buyer and stylist for Miami’s top clothing boutiques and maga zines, but eventually the pull of the great city of London brought her back to the United Kingdom. In 2007, she decided to follow her life-long passion for interior design. It was a natural fit that enabled her to draw on the things that inspire her most, including travel, architecture, fashion, and beautiful objects.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">VJ Hirani - Design Assistant</p>\r\n<p class=\"articleCaption\" style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-190 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/12198090531909861341man-silhouette.svg_.hi_-150x150.png\" alt=\"12198090531909861341man silhouette.svg.hi\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Known for her bold, confident designs as much as her enthusiasm and passion for her chosen field, the co-founder and creative visionary behind recently established Liberty Designs, Nicky brings over 15 years to the new endeavor.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\">Experienced with both residential and commercial properties internationally, the London-based designer draws inspiration from all aspects of life from her exotic travels to attending fashion and trade shows. With an aptitude for \"getting inside her clients\' heads,\" the intrepid adventurer consistently delivers extraordinary interiors that dare to be different.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Craig Proudfoot - Project Director</p>\r\n<p class=\"articleCaption\" style=\"padding-left: 30px; text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/3ce1a25.jpg\"><img class=\" size-thumbnail wp-image-214 alignleft\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/3ce1a25-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"3ce1a25\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>Craig has worked for major architectural practices in both Edinburgh and Antwerp. He has a versatile skills base with over fifteen years experience in various aspects of construction management, project development, design &amp; planning. He spent 5 years as a project co-ordinator for a multi award winning residential development company, calling on architectural and project management skills to orchestrate and deliver efficient construction programmes and high quality building products. Craig holds a bachelor of Arhcitecture (Hons) and diploma in architecture.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Douglas Mackay - Digital Designer</p>\r\n<p class=\"articleCaption\" style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-190 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/12198090531909861341man-silhouette.svg_.hi_-150x150.png\" alt=\"12198090531909861341man silhouette.svg.hi\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Douglas has over 15 years’ experience in the creative industries. His main skills lie in brand identity &amp; development although he has a wealth of knowledge in print, online media and film which he has produced for a wide variety of Edinburgh &amp; London based companies. Douglas is also a professional design consultant specialising in creative direction and holds a BSc (Hons) in Interactive Media Design.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\">[/ezcol_1quarter] [ezcol_3quarter_end]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[/ezcol_3quarter_end]", "", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "61-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-03-17 09:33:21", "2015-03-17 09:33:21", "", "61", "http://welivedthedream.com/dev/61-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("226", "1", "2015-03-17 09:34:43", "2015-03-17 09:34:43", "[vegas id=16 fade=3000 delay=4000 overlay= arrows=yes autoplay=yes poster=no]\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>SERVICES</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">[ezcol_1quarter]</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">BRIEF &amp; PROGRAMMING</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Programming involves understand the spatial requirements needed in a room. How many people occupy the space? What do they do within the space? What is the overall function of the space? Does it have multiple purposes? What fixtures, furnishings, and equipment are needed? What are the lighting requirements? What storage is needed? Ventilation? Heating? Cooling? Special criteria? Age groups using the space? What adjacencies are important? What are the budget constraints? When must the project be completed? All of these answered questions help us solve and tackle the next phase.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">RESEARCH</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Based on the brief from the client and the design team exploring ideas, this is when we research interesting special ideas. This can come in many forms from existing architectural spaces, nature, furniture, lighting and photography. The client will likely have some images or ideas that we can also explore.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">SCHEMATIC DESIGN</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Schematic Design is the first two dimensional exploration of the space. Often we will sketch an idea with the relationship of various elements illustrated on paper. A floor plan may simply be a bubble diagram at this point. It\'s not clearly defined because we are exploring ideas. What if we moved the built-in bookcases to this side of the room or moved the seating area back half a meter, we may even quickly sketch a perspective or a series of elevations to understand the three dimensional space.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">DESIGN DEVELOPMENT</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">This stage is just as it describes....We begin developing the specific design with actual selections. We may have known that we wanted a wing chair in the Schematic Phase, but now we must select and present a specific chair including: manufacturer, price, fabric, etc. On a larger scale, if we were designing a house, we\'d be drawing the plumbing walls, window units, staircase, ceiling details etc. This stage is all about the details and the larger and more complicated the space, the longer this stage will take</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">CONSTRUCTION DOCUMENTATION</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">This phase documents on paper via architectural floor plans, sections, elevations, joinery details, finish legends, flooring patterns, electrical plans, lighting plans, switching diagrams, HVAC layout, plumbing plans, site plans, and specifications the total work to be completed. This phase is critical to a successful project. Designers must put on the drawings and in the specifications what is to go to bid (public) or be priced by a contractor(s). In order to compare apples to apples, the designer must be specific and have everything documented</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">CONSTRUCTION ADMINISTRATION</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">This is the final stage where things are built and installed. Overseeing the \"installation\" to make sure items are received in good condition, installed correctly, and that documents have been followed properly. At this stage we snag a project.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Designing is a process that unfolds in stages and when we skip one part, we may be missing a critical element to the successful completion of the job</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">[/ezcol_1quarter] [ezcol_1quarter]</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">[/ezcol_1quarter] [ezcol_1half_end][/ezcol_1half_end]</p>", "", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "74-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-03-17 09:34:43", "2015-03-17 09:34:43", "", "74", "http://welivedthedream.com/dev/74-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
