INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("452", "1", "2015-07-13 09:51:48", "2015-07-13 09:51:48", "[vegas id=16 fade=3000 delay=4000 overlay= arrows=yes autoplay=yes poster=no]\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>SERVICES</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">[ezcol_1quarter]</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>BRIEF &amp; PROGRAMMING</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Programming involves understanding the spatial requirements needed in a room. How many people occupy the space? What do they do within the space? What is the overall function of the space? Does it have multiple purposes? What fixtures, furnishings, and equipment are needed? What are the lighting requirements? What storage is needed? Ventilation? Heating? Cooling? Special criteria? Age groups using the space? What adjacencies are important? What are the budget constraints? When must the project be completed? Being able to answer these questions helps us to tackle and solve the next phase within projects.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>RESEARCH</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Based on the brief from the client and the design team exploring ideas, this is when we research interesting special ideas. This can come in many forms from existing architectural spaces, nature, furniture, lighting and photography. The client will likely have some images or ideas that we can also explore.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>SCHEMATIC DESIGN</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Schematic Design is the first two dimensional exploration of the space. Often we will sketch an idea with the relationship of various elements illustrated on paper. A floor plan may simply be a bubble diagram at this point. It\'s not clearly defined because we are exploring ideas. What if we moved the built-in bookcases to this side of the room or moved the seating area back half a meter, we may even quickly sketch a perspective or a series of elevations to understand the three dimensional space.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>DESIGN DEVELOPMENT</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">This stage is just as it describes....We begin developing the specific design with actual selections. We may have known that we wanted a wing chair in the Schematic Phase, but now we must select and present a specific chair including: manufacturer, price, fabric, etc. On a larger scale, if we were designing a house, we\'d be drawing the plumbing walls, window units, staircase, ceiling details etc. This stage is all about the details and the larger and more complicated the space, the longer this stage will take.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>CONSTRUCTION DOCUMENTATION</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">This phase documents on paper via architectural floor plans, sections, elevations, joinery details, finish legends, flooring patterns, electrical plans, lighting plans, switching diagrams, HVAC layout, plumbing plans, site plans, and specifications the total work to be completed. This phase is critical to a successful project. Designers must put on the drawings and in the specifications what is to go to bid (public) or be priced by a contractor(s). In order to compare apples to apples, the designer must be specific and have everything documented.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223\" src=\"http://welivedthedream.com/dev/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/divider_2.jpg\" alt=\"divider_2\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>CONSTRUCTION ADMINISTRATION</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">This is the final stage where things are built and installed. Overseeing the \"installation\" to make sure items are received in good condition, installed correctly, and that documents have been followed properly. At this stage we snag a project.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Designing is a process that unfolds in stages and when we skip one part, we may be missing a critical element to the successful completion of the job</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">[/ezcol_1quarter] [ezcol_1quarter]</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">[/ezcol_1quarter] [ezcol_1half_end][/ezcol_1half_end]</p>", "", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "74-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-07-13 09:51:48", "2015-07-13 09:51:48", "", "74", "http://www.nickymurraydesign.com/74-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
